The paper deals with multiuser transmission methods in a low SNR regime, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method involves utilizing knowledge of modulation type, which is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which are commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
